&lt;p&gt;Dermatology Clinical Nurse&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This is the best time to join our team&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a full time Band 5 Dermatology Nurse role for a highly motivated Dermatology position.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Dermatology service is a dynamic, progressive department, with a committed, dedicated and friendly nursing team who are fully supported by our team of Doctors. The service is based at Croydon University.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The dermatology unit provides a range of day care treatments, including phototherapy, photodynamic therapy and topical treatments to patients with acute and chronic skin disease including skin cancer and wounds. The unit has daily clinics and minor surgery and phototherapy. This is an exciting opportunity for an enthusiastic and motivated individual to be supported to develop expertise within this specialty. Experience within a dermatology setting is desirable; however consideration will be given to a candidate who demonstrates a keen interest in developing a career within dermatology and has a proven track record of personal and professional development. You will be joining a team dedicated to providing quality care and we aim to develop and support all our staff to achieve this. The service currently operates Monday-Friday and the post holder will be expected to be fully committed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date : 20th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Fortune Dube, Matron&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email: fortune.dube@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tel: 0208-401 3000 Ext 5653.  Bleep 139&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Availability for informal visits will be from Monday to Friday 08:00 to 16:00 hours. &lt;/p&gt;
